
Based on the following tutorial:
 
  http://www.tutorialspoint.com/svn/index.htm
   
---------------------------------------------------------------
   
Get help information:

  svn help

Checkout an svn repository:

  svn checkout http://svn.server.com/svn/project_repo --username=tom

Look the working directory info:

  cd project_repo
  svn info
  
Check the working directory status:

  svn status
  
Add a file to the pending change list:

  svn add file.dat
 
Commit the changes to the repository:

  svn commit -m "Commit message"

Check the log information of a given revision:

  svn log --revision 14764

Check the difference between the working directory and the repository:

  svn diff
 
Update the working directory:
 
  svn update

Revert the changes made to a given file:

  svn revert file.dat
  
Revert a complete directory

  svn revert -R trunk
  
Create a tag:

  svn copy --revision=4 trunk/ tags/tag_name
 
Create a branch:
  
  svn copy trunk/ branches/branch_name

Merge on branck into trunk:

  cd trunk
  svn merge ../branches/branch_name/



More useful information:

  http://svnbook.red-bean.com/en/1.7/index.html
  http://www.linuxfromscratch.org/blfs/edguide/chapter03.html
  
  